<li id="cite_note-198"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-198">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFAbdussamatov2004" class="citation journal cs1">Abdussamatov, Habibullo I. (June 2004). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1017%2FS1743921304006775">"About the long-term coordinated variations of the activity, radius, total irradiance of the Sun and the Earth's climate"</a>. <i>Proceedings of the International Astronomical Union</i>. <b>223</b>: 541–542. <a href="/wiki/Bibcode_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Bibcode (identifier)">Bibcode</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2004IAUS..223..541A">2004IAUS..223..541A</a>. <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1017%2FS1743921304006775">10.1017/S1743921304006775</a></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Proceedings+of+the+International+Astronomical+Union&amp;rft.atitle=About+the+long-term+coordinated+variations+of+the+activity%2C+radius%2C+total+irradiance+of+the+Sun+and+the+Earth%27s+climate&amp;rft.volume=223&amp;rft.pages=541-542&amp;rft.date=2004-06&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1017%2FS1743921304006775&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F2004IAUS..223..541A&amp;rft.aulast=Abdussamatov&amp;rft.aufirst=Habibullo+I.&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1017%252FS1743921304006775&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+climate+change+science" class="Z3988"></span> "The main cause of climate change during the last millennia is the corresponding cyclic variation of the 80- and 200-year component of irradiance correlated with activity. That is why, the contemporary (climate change) is not anomalous but is ordinary secular global warming."</span>
</li>
