<li><cite id="CITEREFPierceAdams2009" class="citation cs2">Pierce J.R. &amp; P.J. Adams (May 2009), "Can cosmic rays affect cloud condensation nuclei by altering new particle formation rates?", <i>Geophys. Res. Lett.</i>, <b>36</b> (9): L09820, <a href="/wiki/Bibcode_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Bibcode (identifier)">Bibcode</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2009GeoRL..36.9820P">2009GeoRL..36.9820P</a>, <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1029%2F2009GL037946">10.1029/2009GL037946</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/S2CID_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="S2CID (identifier)">S2CID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://api.semanticscholar.org/CorpusID:15704833">15704833</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Geophys.+Res.+Lett.&amp;rft.atitle=Can+cosmic+rays+affect+cloud+condensation+nuclei+by+altering+new+particle+formation+rates%3F&amp;rft.volume=36&amp;rft.issue=9&amp;rft.pages=L09820&amp;rft.date=2009-05&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fapi.semanticscholar.org%2FCorpusID%3A15704833%23id-name%3DS2CID&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1029%2F2009GL037946&amp;rft_id=info%3Abibcode%2F2009GeoRL..36.9820P&amp;rft.au=Pierce+J.R.&amp;rft.au=P.J.+Adams&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+climate+change+science" class="Z3988"></span>. L09820.</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFPittock2009" class="citation cs2">Pittock, B. (October 2009), "Can solar variations explain variations in the Earth's climate? An editorial comment", <i>Climatic Change</i>, <b>96</b> (4): 483–487, <a href="/wiki/Doi_(identifier)" class="mw-redirect" title="Doi (identifier)">doi</a>:<span class="id-lock-free" title="Freely accessible"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://doi.org/10.1007%2Fs10584-009-9645-8">10.1007/s10584-009-9645-8</a></span></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Climatic+Change&amp;rft.atitle=Can+solar+variations+explain+variations+in+the+Earth%27s+climate%3F+An+editorial+comment&amp;rft.volume=96&amp;rft.issue=4&amp;rft.pages=483-487&amp;rft.date=2009-10&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1007%2Fs10584-009-9645-8&amp;rft.au=Pittock%2C+B.&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+climate+change+science" class="Z3988"></span>, pp.&#160;483–487. Referred to by <a href="#CITEREFEPA2009">EPA 2009</a>: <cite class="citation cs2 cs1-prop-long-vol"><i>EPA's Response to Public Comments</i>, vol.&#160;3: Attribution of Observed Climate Change, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.epa.gov/climatechange/endangerment/comments/volume3.html#3-36">Response 3-36, in Sec 3.2.2 Solar Irradiance</a></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=EPA%27s+Response+to+Public+Comments&amp;rft.pages=Response+3-36%2C+in+Sec+3.2.2+Solar+Irradiance&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHistory+of+climate+change+science" class="Z3988"></span></li></ul>
